    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-13T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-13T04:00:00-05:00" n="417"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/1517: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-13T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 13, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 13—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 7, 10 a.m.<note n="10" xml:id="d417fn10">This telegram from the Embassy
                        in China repeated the Department’s telegram No. 141, May 5, 4 p.m., <ref
                            target="#pg_313">p. 313</ref>.</note> In view of the fact that my
                    colleagues, other than German and possibly Japanese, do not intend to comply
                    with the Chinese request regarding land tax as stated in my telegram of May 7, 3
                        p.m.<note n="11" xml:id="d417fn11">Not printed.</note> and confirmed to me
                    again today, is it still desired that Americans be advised to comply with
                    request and pay tax under protest?</p>
                <p>Sent to Embassy, Hankow, repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
